Following the dusk to dawn curfew occasioned by the COVID?19 disease, street families in the country have borne the brunt as their lives have been made intolerable.  however, in meru county, a catholic priest has become a beacon of hope for such starving families, and his mission has been to feed them ever since the curfew started. Our reporter George Maringa caught up with father mugambi who is now a darling to 250 and counting homeless children in meru town.